Fidelity Says U.K. Bank Reforms Discouraging Investors, Sky Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-07T18:53:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/fidelity-says-u-k-bank-reforms-discouraging-investors-sky-says.html
Fidelity International warned U.K.
Chancellor of the Exchequer  George Osborne  in a letter to the
Treasury last month that the growing burden and cost of
regulation, in addition to economic uncertainty, is making it
“difficult to build a compelling investment thesis for U.K.
banks,” Sky News  reported , without saying where it got the
information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 